article.headline: Wright St. 58, Presbyterian 42
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- Todd Brown and Vaughn Duggins each scored 12 points to lead Wright State to a 58-42 win over Presbyterian on Monday night. Will Graham's 3-pointer with 15:15 left in the first half sparked a 21-4 run that gave the Raiders a 26-10 lead, and Presbyterian never recovered. The cold-shooting Blue Hose shot only 33 percent (15 of 41) for the game. The Raiders (15-6), who have won six straight, led by as many as 29 points, 54-28, with 10:04 left in the game. Al'Lonzo Coleman scored 18 points for Presbyterian (3-22).
